      "writtenOn": "2019-07-11T02:10:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "We\u0027re in the !alphaOrCSConversion case... but now that I think about it we\u0027d also have to check that there\u0027s no cross swizzling between alpha and rgb.\n\nThis made me think... suppose we had a from_srgb and a swizzle, what order should they be in? I think it should actually be swizzle then from_srgb (and reverse in the store case). When we swizzle we\u0027re saying the \"x\" channel really represents the \"y\" value. If \"x\" is \"a\" and y is \"b\" then we would want the srgb conversion to happen to \"x\".\n\nConcrete example: \nSay we supported a theoretical srgb 8bit gray format. I think we\u0027d implement loading that as:\n\nload_a8\nswizzle(\"aaa1\")\nfrom_srgb\n\nand storing as:\n\nto_srgb\nluminance_to_alpha (not supported by get_dst_swizzle_and_store currently).\nstore_a8",
      "parentUuid": "0b7f324a_5920bd8f",
      "revId": "b233ef470f8eee0fb3873e49bfdaea316dee80bc",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "047718d4_a94e78e5",
        "filename": "src/gpu/GrDataUtils.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 540,
      "author": {
        "id": 5085
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-07-11T02:13:38Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Actually store side is not as simple as I wrote... we\u0027d want to do the linear-\u003esrgb conversion after the luminance calc.\n\nPerhaps a better example is srgb single channel red.\n\nload_a8\nswizzle(\"a001\")\nfrom_srgb\n\nand\n\nto_srgb\nswizzle(\"100r\")\nstore_a8",
      "parentUuid": "10b50842_25f15eed",
      "revId": "b233ef470f8eee0fb3873e49bfdaea316dee80bc",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
